data.title: Alibaba’s AI Arm Surges 34% While China Commerce Bounces Back
data.description: The company posted a 16% rise in Chinese e-commerce revenue for the period, suggesting it was faring well in a three-way battle with JD.com Inc. and Meituan.  The strong results are likely to encourage investors betting on Alibaba as a leader in artificial intelligence development.  The company has accelerated the release of AI models, culminating in the relaunch of its flagship Qwen mobile app — an effort to replicate the success of OpenAI’s ChatGPT that got off to a fast start this month.
